I always assumed that &lt;article/&gt; was best suited for things like blog/forum posts or articles on a news web site.<br /><br />Otherwise, I would probably use the &lt;section/&gt; element (instead of the suggested &lt;content/&gt; element):<br /><a href="http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/#the-section" class="postlink">http://www.whatwg.org/specs/web-apps/current-work/#the-section</a><br />which is &quot;a generic document or application section. A section, in this context, is a thematic grouping of content, typically with a header, possibly with a footer.&quot;<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forums.whatwg.org/bb3/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=125">mskinner</a> — Sun Jun 24, 2007 12:40 am</p><hr />
